lighten /ˈlaɪtən/

(lightening,lightened,lightens) 

1. V-T/V-I When something lightens or when you lighten it, it becomes less dark in colour. 使变明亮; 变得明亮 

例： The sky began to lighten. 天空开始变得明亮了。 

2. V-T If someone lightens a situation, they make it less serious or less boring. 缓和 

例： Anthony felt the need to lighten the atmosphere. 安东尼觉得需要缓和一下气氛。 

3. V-T/V-I If your attitude or mood lightens , or if someone or something lightens it, they make you feel more cheerful, happy, and relaxed. 使轻松; 变得轻松 

例： As they approached the outskirts of the city, Ella's mood visibly lightened. 随着他们越来越接近市郊，埃拉的心情明显变得轻松了。

